OL,3,CRare behind-the-scenes photos of Harry
OL,4,CPotter set go under the hammer
OL,6,FUntil 1968, when steam trains were
OL,7,Fdecommissioned, Mr Wood shovelled coal
OL,8,Ffor British Rail trains.
OL,10,F'We weren't supposed to take photos'
OL,12,FMr Wood said: "I was a huge steam
OL,13,Ftrain enthusiast and keen to volunteer
OL,14,Fon the engine. Being a fireman takes a
OL,15,Flot of skill.
OL,17,F"You need to know when you are going
OL,18,Fto need a lot of steam and what is
OL,19,Fcoming up, or, as we say, 'know the
OL,20,Froad'. I was happy to get involved."
